Package: ambrosia
Title: Food demand model for the GCAM human-earth systems model
Version: 1.1.5
Authors@R: c(person(given='Robert', family='Link', email='robert.link@pnnl.gov', role=c('aut','cre','lyr','ard')),
    person(given='Stephanie', family='Waldhoff', email='stephanie.waldhoff@pnnl.gov', role=c('aut')),
    person(given='Ryna', family='Cui', email='yiyun.cui@pnnl.gov', role=c('aut')),
    person(given='Jae', family='Edmonds', email='jae@pnnl.gov', role=c('aut')))
Description: The gcamfd package provides a stand-alone implementation of the food demand
    model used in the GCAM human-earth systems model.  In addition to allowing one to run
    food demand scenarios without setting up a full GCAM run, this code is used to calibrate
    the parameters used for food demand in GCAM.
